The paper deals with inapproximability results for graph problems, which are typically studied in theoretical computer science. The use of the Small Set Expansion Hypothesis and the techniques employed suggest that the paper may fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The problems studied involve graphs and their structures, indicating that the paper may also belong to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper may also fall under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) due to the study of complete bipartite subgraphs.
